summary: Australian breakdancer Rachael Gunn, known as Raygun, has sparked controversy following her performance at the Paris Olympics. Despite qualifying for the Games, Raygun's routine received a score of zero, prompting backlash and online hate, which she has described as "devastating." However, one Olympic judge defended her originality. The controversy has raised questions about the selection process and the subjectivity of judging in breakdancing, with many questioning why Raygun was chosen to represent Australia. Despite the criticism, Raygun's performance has gone viral, gaining attention for its unique style and entertainment value. Some commentators have even suggested that she has won the "Meme Olympics" for her memorable moves.
